Thailand Stock Movers: Bank of Ayudhya, Bangchak, UOB Kay Hian

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-25T05:41:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/thailand-stock-movers-bank-of-ayudhya-uob-kay-hian-securities.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. break in
Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 7.49, or 0.7 percent, to 1,053.92, the
first advance in six days.  Bank of Ayudhya Pcl (BAY)  , a commercial lender, gained
3.7 percent to 25 baht, the first advance in six days. The bank
will pay an interim dividend to 0.35 baht per share, it said in
a regulatory filing. That compares with a payout of 0.22 baht a
share in the same period last year.  Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP)  , a state-controlled
Refiner, climbed 2.3 percent to 21.9 baht, set for the largest
increase since Aug. 15. The company is aiming to grow sales
volume by 6 percent in the second half of the year as it
increases production at its refinery to 100,000 barrels a day,
the company said in a presentation to investors. Bangchakâ€™s
crude run averaged about 80,500 barrels a day in the first half
of the year, it said.  UOB Kay Hian Securities ( Thailand ) Pcl (UOBKH TB), a stock
brokerage, jumped 11 percent to 4.34 baht, poised for the
highest close since July 2008. Net income tripled to 35.9
million baht ($1.2 million) in the second quarter from 10.1
million baht in the same period a year earlier, the company said
in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
